"""
app/mme_scalpx/main.py

Single canonical bootstrap and orchestration entrypoint for ScalpX MME.

Frozen contract
---------------
This module OWNS:
- process bootstrap sequencing
- settings load
- logging bootstrap
- shutdown signal wiring
- clock lifecycle bootstrap
- Redis runtime bootstrap
- Redis connectivity validation
- optional consumer-group bootstrap
- shared application context construction
- per-service runtime context construction
- runtime service supervision
- single-service execution
- lightweight doctor/status reporting
- best-effort application shutdown
- strict runtime service module validation (import, run(context) signature, location)

This module DOES NOT own:
- Redis naming contracts
- schema definitions
- serialization
- broker APIs
- instrument/domain logic
- service business logic
- alternate bootstrap roots
- integration worker orchestration
- domain worker orchestration
- service-specific builder helpers

Design contract
---------------
- main.py is the ONLY composition root.
- All spine imports come from app.mme_scalpx.core.*
- Only frozen runtime services under app.mme_scalpx.services.* are supervised here.
- integrations/login.py is NOT a runtime supervised service.
- domain/instruments.py is NOT a runtime supervised service.
- ops/ is helper-only and not a second root.
- Runtime behavior comes from settings.py and explicit dependency registration only.
- Redis transport behavior remains owned by redisx.py.
- Clock lifecycle remains owned by clock.py.
- Replay mode requires an explicit replay wall-time anchor.
- Shutdown is explicit, cooperative, and idempotent.
- Every supervised runtime module MUST export a callable run(context).
- Module paths must not drift to pluralized or stale names (e.g., reports.py).

Important dependency rule
-------------------------
feeds.py and execution.py require external runtime dependencies that are NOT
defined by settings.py:

- feeds.py requires:
  - context.runtime_instruments / context.instrument_set
  - context.feed_adapter / context.market_data_adapter
- execution.py requires:
  - context.broker

To avoid guessed config fields and guessed factory surfaces, this module uses
an explicit dependency registration layer:

    register_bootstrap_dependencies(
        runtime_instruments=<RuntimeInstrumentSet>,
        feed_adapter=<market data adapter>,
        broker=<broker adapter>,
    )

This registration does NOT create an alternate startup root. It only supplies
external objects required by frozen runtime service contracts before main()
starts supervision.
"""

